The paper deals with designing agents that can explore their environments intelligently, which is a problem in artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a hierarchical design of the agent's policy to affect its exploration capabilities, which falls under the category of reinforcement learning and robotics. The paper also proposes a metric to measure the complexity of the environment, which is related to graph theory and complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.RO. The paper also deals with navigation and proposes a hierarchical approach, which is related to computer vision and systems and control. Therefore, cs.SY and cs.CV are also likely sub-categories.
